            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Due to the error reported in #1933 concerning some widely used clients I fixed this for GET requests.\n\nBut actually nowhere in RFC2616 does it say POST and / or PUT must have a body content. However there are currently test cases testing this behavior and I did not want to introduce a breaking change in a pull request without prior discussion. Can someone who is familiar with the discussion fill me in why it is required that a POST request with an empty body fails?\n\nSpecifically I am refering to the following test cases:\n\n```\ntest_post_empty_json_wont_add_exception_to_response_if_no_debug\ntest_post_empty_json_adds_exception_to_response_content_in_debug\n```\n"
        },
